We here at Dan Kays Auto repair, ( down the Street from Depot Park on SE 4th ) Absolutely love the Unique Culture and the Convenience of a nearby Lunch Spot. We've been lacking on Variety and Convenience in this section of town for sometime now.  Definitely worth your time to stop in and try some of the Various food and drinks.
The quesadilla was delicious!
It's a quaint place and the hot food is tasty. They have quality vegan and vegetarian options. Downside...imo it's priced like a convenience store for their snacks, a significant markup.
Best breakfast burritos!

This was my first visit to Pop-a-Top and I want to start off by saying the food was really good!  What made me a bit frustrated was the staff’s  understanding and communication on allergens.  I had originally asked if a specific menu item used red onions since I have an intolerance (and I told the cashier this), and they said it did. So, I ordered another item on the board that didn’t have onions in the descriptor. When the item came out, it had red onions on top. Thankfully, I was able to pick them off but it was frustrating that I communicated my inability to eat something and staff didn’t follow through in warning me or communicating with me that the item I chose had red onion on it.  I appreciate all the vegan options here though, and the atmosphere is really cool! It was just the food experience that bummed me out a bit.
Prices are RIDICULOUS for a cookie!!! I can go to Walmart and get a whole roll of cookie dough for the price of one cookie!

Love the options here for all kinds of dietary needs. Friendly and quick service. Tons of tasty food either prepackaged or served fresh. Really nice atmosphere, I tend to see families spending time at Depot Park stopping in for a quick bite. Lots to look at while you’re inside. A little cramped but it works out. Highly recommended!
This place has the best bottle openers staff is  very nice and have great stuff for a great prices.

It's a good place if you know your brands... They carry too old of unions in brand name food though.... Stop here every week for coffee and a sweet treat. Good stuff for lunch too. Nice outdoor seating and a little inside too. Nice staff.

Their food is delicious; there's a wide selection of options that really do cater to any kind of food specialty I can think of. Owned by the same owner as the Top, so this is the same quality of food in a bodega setting. Pro tip: breakfast sandwiches and pastries are half off in the afternoons.

I stop by every day for lunch and I can say the rotation that have of food is really amazing. Lots of variety and great flavor. In particular I love their savory pockets and soups, and their great selection of beer (that I don't get because I'm working ☹️)  . Plus, the staff is really friendly and nice. It will always be my work lunch place.
